    <item>
      <title>Re: noob chanter question about charming</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Enchanters&amp;message.id=6169#M6169</link>
      <description>Gear you should work on:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;AC/HP gear.  At your level it is possible to get enough AC and HP to make a HUGE survivability difference.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Cha gear.  Cha effects the resist rate of your spells.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Int gear.  Try to hit "200 int".  Int above 200 isn't really worth bothering with.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The "Blue Ceramic Band".  It is a pottery recipie.  If you are keen, look up the ingredients, buy them (they are all vendor-sold), and hire a potter to combine them for you.  (when asking for the potter, make sure you have all the ingredients and mention the item (Blue Ceramic Band) and that you have all of the ingredients ready).&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;You can test to see if you have all of the ingredients (without bothering a potter) by attempting a combine by yourself.  It will destroy the ingredients if you have the correct ones, but will ensure that you know that the right recipie.  =-)  And being polite to people you are asking for help is important!</description>
      <pubDate>Sun, 01 Jan 2006 18:38:26 GMT</pubDate>
