      <title>Re: noob chanter question about charming</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Enchanters&amp;message.id=6149#M6149</link>
      <description>I think there's a post somewhere on those forums that explains how much exp you get charming depending on how much damage you doing. Basically the more damage you do, the better the exp. &lt;br&gt;Easier on the exp side when you do reverse charming (you drop your pet hps, get rid of charm, park the former pet/or kill former pet, you take another pet etc) i think.</description>
      <pubDate>Fri, 23 Dec 2005 11:16:01 GMT</pubDate>
