    <item>
      <title>Re: noob chanter question about charming</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Enchanters&amp;message.id=6150#M6150</link>
      <description>Reverse charming is, frankly, too much work for pre-charm-nerf content.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;The clicky ring you're looking for is a Blue Ceramic Band. It's cheap, and clickable at level 20.  If you can't find on in the bazaar, any decent potter should be able to whip one up for you.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Getting charisma up will definitely help with charms, as will tashing first, and charming things that are not very magic resistant, and lower level than you.  It will still be somewhat unreliable for long durations at your level however, so I suggest killing in pairs (Letting a mob beat your pet down to near 0, letting your pet doing likewise to the mob, then killing both.)</description>
      <pubDate>Fri, 23 Dec 2005 19:51:06 GMT</pubDate>
